  • Property Details

    • coverPage

      @NotNull public @NotNull javafx.beans.property.ObjectProperty<UIPage<?>> coverPageProperty

      Returns the property containing the Cover Page assigned to this UIPageHandler.

      Details

      1. The UIPage that is displayed if no pages have been added to this UIPageHandler.
      2. A UIPageHandler is considered empty when its Page List is empty.
      3. If this UIPageHandler does not have a Cover Page, the returned property will contain null.
      See Also:
      getCoverPage(), setCoverPage(UIPage)

    • visiblePageBinding

      @NotNull public @NotNull javafx.beans.binding.ObjectBinding<UIPage<?>> visiblePageBinding()

      Returns a convenience binding containing the UIPage that is currently displayed by this UIPageHandler.

      Details

      1. If available, the last page in this UIPageHandlers Page List is displayed.
      2. If this UIPageHandlers Page List is empty, the Cover Page is displayed instead.
      3. If this UIPageHandlers Page List is empty AND this UIPageHandler has no Cover Page, then no page is displayed, and the ObjectBinding returned by this method will contain null.
      4. The logic for calculating the contents of the BooleanBinding returned by this method is contained within calcVisiblePage().
      Returns:
      A convenience binding containing the UIPage that is currently displayed by this UIPageHandler.

    • containsPage

      public boolean containsPage​(UIPage<?> page)

      Checks if this UIPageHandler contains the specified UIPage or not.

      Details

      1. This method is synchronized.

      Return Definition

      1. If the specified UIPage is null, return false.
      2. If this UIPageHandlers Page List contains the specified UIPage, return true.
      3. If the specified UIPage is this UIPageHandlers Cover Page, return true.
      4. Otherwise, return false.
      Parameters:
      page - The UIPage being checked.
      Returns:
      True if this UIPageHandler contains the specified UIPage, false if it does not.

    • turnTo

      public boolean turnTo​(@Nullable @Nullable UIPage<?> page)

      Turns this UIPageHandler to the specified UIPage.

      Details

      1. If the specified UIPage is null, this method does nothing and returns false silently.
      2. If the specified UIPage is in the Page List, all pages after the specified UIPage are removed.
      3. If the specified UIPage is the Cover Page, the Page List is cleared.
      4. Otherwise, the specified UIPage is instead passed to turnToNew(UIPage).
      Parameters:
      page - The UIPage being turned to.
      Returns:
      True if the specified UIPage was successfully turned to, false if it was not.

    • turnToNew

      public void turnToNew​(@NotNull @NotNull UIPage<?> page)

      Adds the specified UIPage to this UIPageHandler.

      Details

      1. If the specified UIPage is null, a NullPointerException is thrown.
      2. If the specified UIPage is the Cover Page, an UnsupportedOperationException is thrown.
      3. If the specified UIPage has already been added to the Page List, an UnsupportedOperationException is thrown.
      4. Otherwise, the specified UIPage is added to the Page List.
      Parameters:
      page - The UIPage being turned to.

    • backUnchecked

      public UIPage<?> backUnchecked()
